Senior players grace such tournaments and their sense of responsibility rubs off on the rest of the youngsters.Handas served as chairman and organiser of the tournament till his death in 2017. The current leadership has kept the founders’  vision for youth football alive.  Youth tournaments, particularly those held countrywide during December holidays, make for a thrilling spectacle.  They are a melting pot of raw talent and have given rise to some of Kenya’s best players.
To retired players, such tournaments are a perfect forum to meet and reminisce about beautiful moments in the game from years gone by.



