The raw energy and talent in ragtag teams of young men and women playing in such off-season tournaments is amazing. In such tournaments, young men and women often fight their hearts out for modest prizes, and the winning team gets a cash token to be shared out by the players, and football equipment like pairs of boots and kits.





Fans in full cheer during the opening day of the Chris Oguso Super Cup in Vihiga County. The annual tournament reaches its climax with the finals this weekend at Chavavo High School. 
Photo credit: File | Nation Media Group


In Nairobi, off-season football tournaments like Dagoretti Super Cup (at Riruta and NCC play grounds), Koth Biro (Ziwani), Kiko Cup (Woodley grounds in Kibra) and Otty Father Cup (Jericho) provide a platform for young players to brush shoulders with Kenyan Premier League players.



