The good book says in Luke 12:48 that to whom much is given, much will be required. If (and this is a big “if”) much has been given to our professional footballers, much is expected of them by way of  acting as role models for the new crop of players.
The established players grace such tournaments and more often than not, their team work, sense of responsibility, diligence  with which they execute the task at hand, and work ethic  rubs off on the rest of the youngsters. That has been the case, particularly with Koth Biro and Dagoretti Super Cup. Koth Biro football tournament,  first held in 1978, is held annually from November to January.



